<div id="content">
    <h3>Why send thank you notes?</h3>
    
    <div id="thank-help-expanded"<% if !current_mpd_user.show_thank_help %>style="display: none;"<% end %>>
        <p>When I think about sending thank you notes, I think about how much 
            God has provided for me.</p>

        <p>"Let the peace of Christ rule in your hearts, since as members of one 
            body you were called to peace. And be thankful.  Let the word of 
            Christ dwell in you richly as you teach and admonish one another 
            with all wisdom, and as you sing psalms, hymns and spiritual songs 
            with gratitude in your hearts to God.  And whatever you do, whether 
            in word or deed, do it all in the name of the Lord Jesus, giving 
            thanks to God the Father through him. (Col 3:15-17)</p>

        <p>As we see in this passage, that thankfulness starts in your heart!  
            It is really hard to think about thanking people when we feel we 
            deserve something, but when we understand thankfulness in our hearts 
            and give Christ control of our hearts then thankfulness will 
            overflow from us.  </p>

        <p>Not only is this crucial, but being thankful and expressing that to 
            God and others is God's will (I Thes. 5:18).  Thanking others helps 
            us become more thankful for what God is doing in our lives and how 
            much He has given to us.  It also is a great way to minister to the 
            giving party.  When someone gives something to us, they are probably 
            not looking for thanks, but when they receive thanks it brings great 
            joy to their heart.</p>

        <p>Think about it from God's view.  When we thank God for all he has 
            done, it brings great joy to His heart, so why wouldn't we pass that 
            one to our friends and family.</p>

        <p>Remember God who calls is faithful (I Thes. 5:24).  He will provide 
            in His way and in His timing for His glory.  We want to pause to 
            give thanks to His people as they become His means of provision for 
            us to go on summer projects around the world. [ 
            <%= link_to_remote("hide this text", :url => {:action => "toggle_show_thank_help"}) %> ]</p>
    </div>

    <div id="thank-help-collapsed" <% if current_mpd_user.show_thank_help %>style="display: none;"<% end %>>
