<div id="sidebar">
    <h3>A few helpful hints</h3>

    <h4>What to Include in Your Thank You Note</h4>
    
    <ul>
        <li>Hand-write the note on personal or nice stationery &mdash; if 
            someone takes the time to hand write a check, then we should take 
            the time to hand write the thanks</li>
        <li>Write the exact date in the upper right-hand corner</li>
        <li>Express appreciation for the gift, including the exact amount of 
            the gift.  This lets them know that you received the amount they 
            intended to give and that it's significant to you because you 
            noticed the amount.</li>
        <li>Describe what the gift will help achieve</li>
        <li>Include something personal in the note</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Sample Thank You Note</h4>
    
    <p style="text-align: right">May 10, 1999</p>
    
    <p>Dear Dr. and Mrs. Smith,</p>
    <p>Thank you for your gift of $100 to support my ministry this summer.  Your
        prayers and finances are greatly appreciated.  Your investment will have 
        far-reaching results as I help reach people for Christ!</p>
    <p>Please join me in praying that God would continually deepen my commitment
        to the cause of Christ.  Your prayers are very important.  Thanks again
        for your help.</p>
    <p style="text-align: right">In Christ,</p>
</div>
